**REPAIRED CODE**:

```
#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
char a[100005];
int main()
{
    cin>>a;
    int len=strlen(a),ans=0;
    for(int i=1;i<len;i++)
        if(a[i]!=a[i-1])
            ans++;
    cout<<ans<<endl;
    return 0;
}
```

The problem with the initial code is that the `ans` variable is not initialized before being used. I have initialized it to 0 in the repaired code.